SolutionNote that taking the reciprocal of both sides gives \begin{align*}\dfrac1{x_{n+2}}&=\dfrac{x_n^2+x_{n+1}^2}{2x_nx_{n+1}(x_n+x_{n+1})}\\&=\dfrac{(x_n+x_{n+1})^2-2x_nx_{n+1}}{2x_nx_{n+1}(x_n+x_{n+1})}=\dfrac{x_n+x_{n+1}}{2x_nx_{n+1}}-\dfrac1{x_n+x_{n+1}}.\end{align*}

Summing this from $n=1$ to infinity gives \begin{align*}\sum_{n=1}^\infty\dfrac1{x_{n+2}}&=\sum_{n=1}^\infty\dfrac{x_n+x_{n+1}}{2x_nx_{n+1}}-\sum_{n=1}^\infty\dfrac1{x_n+x_{n+1}}\\\sum_{n=1}^\infty\dfrac1{x_n}-\dfrac1{x_1}-\dfrac1{x_2}&=\sum_{n=1}^\infty\dfrac{x_n+x_{n+1}}{2x_nx_{n+1}}-\sum_{n=1}^\infty\dfrac1{x_n+x_{n+1}}\\\sum_{n=1}^\infty\dfrac1{x_n}-33&=\sum_{n=1}^\infty\dfrac{x_n+x_{n+1}}{2x_nx_{n+1}}-\sum_{n=1}^\infty\dfrac1{x_n+x_{n+1}}.\end{align*}  Isolating the summation we want and watching magic happen gives \begin{align*}\sum_{n=1}^\infty\dfrac1{x_n+x_{n+1}}&=\sum_{n=1}^\infty\left(\dfrac{x_n+x_{n+1}}{2x_nx_{n+1}}-\dfrac1{x_n}\right)+33\\&=\sum_{n=1}^\infty\dfrac{x_n-x_{n+1}}{2x_nx_{n+1}}+33\\&=\dfrac12\sum_{n=1}^\infty\left(\dfrac1{x_{n+1}}-\dfrac1{x_n}\right)+33.\end{align*} The summation on the RHS is a telescoping series, so almost all the terms cancel out and we are left with a final answer of $-\tfrac1{2x_1}+33=\boxed{23}.$

